WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.136
[scribbling]

2
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.723
[scribbling]

3
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.727
[hip-hop music playing]

4
00:00:18.810 --> 00:00:19.936
[Cam] In the family business.

5
00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:23.148
sometimes you gotta do shitty things
to the people that you love.

6
00:00:24.649 --> 00:00:28.820
Then again. is it that bad
to tell my sister I'm taking my job back?

7
00:00:30.447 --> 00:00:31.281
[door slams]

8
00:00:31.364 --> 00:00:34.659
I mean. I never told her
this was a permanent thing.

9
00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.621
And she's gonna land on her feet.

10
00:00:38.705 --> 00:00:40.832
Being a chick nowadays is
actually an advant--

11
00:00:40.915 --> 00:00:42.792
-Isla needs to talk to you.
-Fuck! Jesus Christ!

12
00:00:44.502 --> 00:00:46.129
[inhales]

13
00:00:51.968 --> 00:00:53.261
What's going on?

14
00:00:53.344 --> 00:00:54.471
We need to talk.

15
00:00:55.263 --> 00:00:56.306
Sandy get dumped again?

16
00:00:56.389 --> 00:00:58.558
We don't need a family meeting
every time this happens.

17
00:00:58.641 --> 00:01:00.018
Have a seat. Cam.

18
00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:06.733
[Cam] So. what's up?

19
00:01:08.026 --> 00:01:12.447
You embezzled $2 million
and are an active drug user.

20
00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:15.533
and you cannot be
the president of the Los Angeles Waves.

21
00:01:15.617 --> 00:01:16.493
[chuckles]

22
00:01:16.993 --> 00:01:18.620
What are you talking about?

23
00:01:18.703 --> 00:01:19.621
Cam!

24
00:01:20.455 --> 00:01:22.040
Don't do this. We know.

25
00:01:25.168 --> 00:01:26.419
You motherfucking snitches.

26
00:01:26.961 --> 00:01:29.589
And I will sue your ass
for wrongful termination.

27
00:01:29.672 --> 00:01:31.091
You cannot prove any of this shit.

28
00:01:31.174 --> 00:01:32.133
Jackie.

29
00:01:32.634 --> 00:01:35.220
Cam. I'm only doing this because
I hope you get the help you need.

30
00:01:38.264 --> 00:01:39.516
[Cam] Come on.

31
00:01:39.599 --> 00:01:42.185
I've been using your piss
for a month now. Nobody's caught on.

32
00:01:42.268 --> 00:01:44.104
Keep your mouth shut. and we'll be good.

33
00:01:44.729 --> 00:01:48.108
You were… recording me?

34
00:01:49.067 --> 00:01:50.235
-You fucking…
-[Ness] Hey! Stop

35
00:01:50.318 --> 00:01:51.486
You little shit!

36
00:01:51.569 --> 00:01:52.946
I'm gonna fuckin' murder you.

37
00:01:53.029 --> 00:01:54.572
-Cam! Cam!
-[Ness. Sandy grunt]

38
00:01:54.656 --> 00:01:56.199
-[Cam] I gave you my steak!
-[Ness] Stop!

39
00:01:56.282 --> 00:01:58.076
-Cam!
-Get off!

40
00:01:58.159 --> 00:01:59.119
Stop it! Stop it!

41
00:01:59.202 --> 00:02:00.411
Just don't touch him.

42
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:07.418
You have no idea how hard it is
to be the oldest in this family.

43
00:02:08.169 --> 00:02:10.421
You would all be crackheads

44
00:02:10.505 --> 00:02:13.258
if you had to deal with
the shit that I went through.

45
00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:15.301
Dad was so good to you.

46
00:02:15.385 --> 00:02:17.095
But he put me through hell.

47
00:02:17.178 --> 00:02:19.472
Then he hands me
some sinking ship of a team

48
00:02:19.556 --> 00:02:20.807
right before he croaks.

49
00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:24.185
And I still… I still managed
to squeak out a couple championships.

50
00:02:24.269 --> 00:02:26.062
and I was under pressure.

51
00:02:26.729 --> 00:02:27.647
So yeah.

52
00:02:27.730 --> 00:02:31.818
I turned to some friendly.
natural. cocoa-based narcotics

53
00:02:31.901 --> 00:02:33.111
to help me get through it.

54
00:02:33.194 --> 00:02:37.407
I'm sure it was a lot. Cam.
and I'm sorry for how Dad treated you.

55
00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:39.909
but it doesn't change
the current situation.

56
00:02:39.993 --> 00:02:42.620
I'll stop.
Look. it's not gonna happen again.

57
00:02:42.704 --> 00:02:44.164
I'll call Rob Lowe.

58
00:02:44.247 --> 00:02:46.749
I'll go hiking with him.
you know. get on his program.

59
00:02:46.833 --> 00:02:50.044
Look. the guy who attacked Jackie.
that's the old Cam. This is the new one.

60
00:02:50.128 --> 00:02:53.047
Cam. you stole from your own family.

61
00:02:53.131 --> 00:02:57.427
blackmailed Sandy.
and used Jackie to violate your probation.

62
00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:00.638
I've notified Stephen and the other
board members about your behavior.

63
00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:02.515
The deal with Fleischman is dead.

64
00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:05.101
Bernie will handle
the sale of your shares to the rest of us.

65
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:08.730
And if you want to watch a game.
you can watch it from home.

66
00:03:08.813 --> 00:03:10.815
[soft funky pop music playing]

67
00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:14.903
You were dying to piss into that cup

68
00:03:14.986 --> 00:03:16.946
as long as you thought
you could get your beak wet.

69
00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:19.616
And you.
you covered up that payment for me.

70
00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:21.659
So you are just as guilty as I am.

71
00:03:21.743 --> 00:03:23.494
Cam. back off.

72
00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:25.079
And you were never my favorite.

73
00:03:25.163 --> 00:03:26.247
Second favorite?

74
00:03:26.331 --> 00:03:27.290
Third.

75
00:03:27.373 --> 00:03:28.708
[gasps softly]

76
00:03:28.791 --> 00:03:32.837
Dad is looking up at us right now.
and he is ashamed.

77
00:03:40.678 --> 00:03:42.680
You're all such fucking losers.

78
00:03:44.933 --> 00:03:46.935
["Heavy. California" by Jungle playing]

79
00:03:51.814 --> 00:03:53.691
[Isla] Let's try this again.

80
00:03:53.775 --> 00:03:56.277
It's been about a month
since Cam left the organization.

81
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:58.321
and things have been pretty great.

82
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.156
How great?

83
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:03.451
Well. we made the fucking finals.
That's right.

84
00:04:04.244 --> 00:04:08.164
First. we took out Phoenix. then Houston.

85
00:04:08.748 --> 00:04:11.918
The conference finals against Seattle
were closer than I'd have liked.

86
00:04:12.001 --> 00:04:15.797
but we're on the brink
of being world champs.

87
00:04:15.880 --> 00:04:19.884
Also. the guy I've been dating
long distance is actually in town.

88
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:22.262
The tricky thing is he's here because

89
00:04:23.263 --> 00:04:25.640
well. we're playing each other
in the finals.

90
00:04:25.723 --> 00:04:28.268
[music continues]

91
00:04:28.351 --> 00:04:32.188
LA versus Boston.
the greatest rivalry in all of basketball.

92
00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:34.148
I gotta say. Isla Gordon did it.

93
00:04:34.232 --> 00:04:35.692
You know. Sean's kinda growing on me.

94
00:04:35.775 --> 00:04:39.320
Unfortunately for her.
Boston is gonna take LA to pound town.

95
00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:41.281
This thing is gonna be Sweep City USA.

96
00:04:41.364 --> 00:04:42.949
Never mind. Still a moron.

97
00:04:43.032 --> 00:04:45.493
Hey. don't listen to him.
You guys are looking good.

98
00:04:45.576 --> 00:04:46.786
You dominated the playoffs.

99
00:04:46.869 --> 00:04:48.204
I don't know about that.

100
00:04:48.288 --> 00:04:50.415
I mean.
Chicago had me sweating for a minute.

101
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:51.332
Oh.

102
00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.419
Chicago and I have that in common.

103
00:04:54.919 --> 00:04:58.172
[Isla] Is it smart to get attached
to a guy living across the country

104
00:04:58.256 --> 00:05:01.592
who happens to coach
the team I hate most in the world?

105
00:05:01.676 --> 00:05:02.552
I don't know.

106
00:05:02.635 --> 00:05:04.679
But we've agreed to just be in the moment.

107
00:05:04.762 --> 00:05:06.806
Although tonight's moment is game one.

108
00:05:06.889 --> 00:05:09.267
Okay. my ride is on the way.

109
00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:12.562
and so there are no eyewitnesses.
it's one of those driverless cars.

110
00:05:12.645 --> 00:05:14.439
Those things are covered in cameras.

111
00:05:15.481 --> 00:05:16.316
Oh yeah.

112
00:05:16.399 --> 00:05:20.111
But what we really need to talk about
is how this is gonna work

113
00:05:20.194 --> 00:05:21.738
now that the finals have started.

114
00:05:21.821 --> 00:05:24.490
Okay. well.
knowing how competitive you are.

115
00:05:24.574 --> 00:05:27.702
maybe we shouldn't talk about basketball
until the series is over.

116
00:05:27.785 --> 00:05:28.745
What?

117
00:05:28.828 --> 00:05:31.289
I am way less competitive than you are.

118
00:05:31.372 --> 00:05:33.708
You're being competitive
about who's less competitive.

119
00:05:33.791 --> 00:05:35.460
Yeah. and I'm winning.

120
00:05:35.543 --> 00:05:36.502
Mm-hmm.

121
00:05:38.796 --> 00:05:39.797
Okay.

122
00:05:41.549 --> 00:05:42.675
That's a good point.

123
00:05:42.759 --> 00:05:43.885
[chuckles]

124
00:05:43.968 --> 00:05:45.136
No basketball talk.

125
00:05:45.636 --> 00:05:46.471
Deal.

126
00:05:46.554 --> 00:05:47.722
-[phone chimes]
-Ooh.

127
00:05:49.223 --> 00:05:51.684
Oh. my. uh. ride just updated.

128
00:05:51.768 --> 00:05:54.729
New one on the way. 18 minutes.

129
00:05:56.105 --> 00:05:57.815
So…

130
00:05:57.899 --> 00:05:58.733
[chuckling]

131
00:06:03.112 --> 00:06:05.073
[upbeat pop music playing]

132
00:06:09.452 --> 00:06:11.746
And here's the itinerary
for your pre-draft scouting trip.

133
00:06:11.829 --> 00:06:13.664
-You leave right after the finals.
-[Ness] Okay.

134
00:06:13.748 --> 00:06:14.791
Jebjana?

135
00:06:15.583 --> 00:06:16.501
Ljubljana.

136
00:06:16.584 --> 00:06:18.920
Ljubljana to Belgrade to Croatia?

137
00:06:19.003 --> 00:06:21.130
I thought you'd wanna see
that small forward from Split.

138
00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:24.425
-Marco Kukoc? Good call.
-His combine stats were off the charts.

139
00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:25.385
Okay.

140
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:28.721
Whose idea was it to book the Four Seasons
and the Ritz for our games in Boston?

141
00:06:28.805 --> 00:06:30.056
That seems excessive. guys.

142
00:06:30.139 --> 00:06:31.182
Sandy. it's the finals.

143
00:06:31.265 --> 00:06:34.143
Everyone's family's there. We need one
hotel for wives and one for mistresses.

144
00:06:34.227 --> 00:06:36.354
Yeah. if anything.
we should be adding an Embassy Suites

145
00:06:36.437 --> 00:06:37.855
-for any surprise local hoochie.
-Yeah.

146
00:06:37.939 --> 00:06:39.982
Dude. what is going on with you?

147
00:06:40.066 --> 00:06:40.983
Fine.

148
00:06:41.484 --> 00:06:44.737
It's just. I am under a microscope here
okay. with this Cam stuff.

149
00:06:44.821 --> 00:06:46.823
I can't bring any more attention
to our expenses.

150
00:06:46.906 --> 00:06:51.160
Okay. Bro. we talked about this. okay?
You did the right thing. You're fine.

151
00:06:51.244 --> 00:06:52.620
Yeah. Also. who are you afraid of?

152
00:06:52.703 --> 00:06:55.957
The only other person who knows is Cam.
and he's not gonna expose himself. right?

153
00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:59.377
Right. yeah. It's just Cam. me. and Aruna.

154
00:06:59.877 --> 00:07:01.045
-Aruna?
-Aruna?

155
00:07:01.129 --> 00:07:02.422
Is that bad?

156
00:07:02.505 --> 00:07:04.507
[upbeat music playing]

157
00:07:04.632 --> 00:07:06.467
[John] There's a timeout
on the floor.

158
00:07:06.551 --> 00:07:08.678
Game one of the finals has been a classic.

159
00:07:08.761 --> 00:07:11.514
Boston leads LA by one
with ten seconds left.

160
00:07:11.597 --> 00:07:14.600
-Do you have any more gum? I'm out.
-You ate my entire pack.

161
00:07:14.684 --> 00:07:16.102
It's okay. I got you.

162
00:07:16.185 --> 00:07:17.478
You could be sitting in the lucky seat.

163
00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:18.646
[phone vibrates]

164
00:07:18.729 --> 00:07:21.482
[Sofia] I got the air purifier!
Now you'll be able to sleep at my place.

165
00:07:22.066 --> 00:07:24.610
Have you told Isla
you're gonna spend the summer in DC?

166
00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:27.530
[Jackie] Not yet. Close game.
Call you after.

167
00:07:27.613 --> 00:07:28.865
-[buzzer blares]
-[Ali] Oh.

168
00:07:28.948 --> 00:07:30.533
-Here we go.
-[Marcus] Waves on three!

169
00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:31.659
One. two. three. waves!

170
00:07:31.742 --> 00:07:32.952
Let's go!

171
00:07:33.035 --> 00:07:34.120
[crowd cheering]

172
00:07:34.203 --> 00:07:35.371
[whistle blows]

173
00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:36.873
Come on. Tommy.

174
00:07:38.374 --> 00:07:40.376
[analyst] Let's see
what Norm drew up. John.

175
00:07:40.877 --> 00:07:42.753
Set the pick! Set the pick!

176
00:07:44.046 --> 00:07:46.215
It's going to Marcus!
It's going to Marcus!

177
00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:50.052
[John] Boston double-teams Marcus.
who has to lay it off to Gibbs.

178
00:07:50.136 --> 00:07:52.096
-For the win!
-[buzzer blares]

179
00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:53.347
No good.

180
00:07:53.431 --> 00:07:55.475
Boston takes game one.

181
00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:57.643
[analyst] Jay Brown read
that play perfectly.

182
00:07:57.727 --> 00:07:58.853
Good job. Good job. Good job.

183
00:07:58.936 --> 00:08:01.814
[analyst] Oh. and it looks like
Winfield has tweaked something.

184
00:08:01.898 --> 00:08:03.608
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. What is it?

185
00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:09.572
[knocking]

186
00:08:14.785 --> 00:08:17.288
I. uh. got some hot chicken for Isla.

187
00:08:18.664 --> 00:08:21.042
I believe
I asked for a no-contact delivery.

188
00:08:21.125 --> 00:08:23.544
Oh. there's gonna be contact.

189
00:08:23.628 --> 00:08:25.505
[romantic music playing]

190
00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:34.430
[romantic music fades]

191
00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:35.556
It's his meniscus.

192
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:37.266
Right now. it's just a partial tear.

193
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:41.103
but if he keeps playing on it.
it could become catastrophic.

194
00:08:41.187 --> 00:08:42.480
Is he done for the season?

195
00:08:42.563 --> 00:08:45.775
-There's no way I'm sitting out.
-I'm not surprised he's saying that.

196
00:08:45.858 --> 00:08:48.778
It looks like he's been playing
on this injury for months.

197
00:08:48.861 --> 00:08:50.655
I'm fine. I had my own guy look at it.

198
00:08:50.738 --> 00:08:51.697
Your own guy?

199
00:08:51.781 --> 00:08:53.824
What the fuck. Marcus?
I thought we were boys.

200
00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:54.742
Me too.

201
00:08:55.409 --> 00:08:58.287
We got a fun working relationship. right?

202
00:08:58.371 --> 00:09:01.165
Like… like Murtaugh and Riggs
in Lethal Weapon. That was us.

203
00:09:01.249 --> 00:09:02.750
Wait. Who's who?

204
00:09:02.833 --> 00:09:04.335
He's Danny Glover. I'm… I'm Mel Gibson.

205
00:09:04.418 --> 00:09:06.963
-But he's the younger one.
-Norm. Dr. Haber.

206
00:09:07.797 --> 00:09:08.798
Can you excuse us?

207
00:09:08.881 --> 00:09:09.966
-Yeah.
-[Dr. Haber] Yeah.

208
00:09:13.844 --> 00:09:17.390
-Marcus. you can't play.
-I don't agree with your assessment.

209
00:09:17.473 --> 00:09:20.893
I'm sorry. but you are not helping us
limping around out there.

210
00:09:21.394 --> 00:09:23.980
[melancholy music playing]

211
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:25.523
What if this is my last shot?

212
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.110
It may be your last shot.

213
00:09:30.903 --> 00:09:33.239
but it could be
some of your teammates' only shot.

214
00:09:33.322 --> 00:09:35.950
So I'm missing a little cushion.
Look. Isla…

215
00:09:39.287 --> 00:09:40.913
I need to be out there.

216
00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:44.250
Please.

217
00:09:46.335 --> 00:09:48.004
I'm banning you from playing.

218
00:09:48.087 --> 00:09:51.465
Focus on getting better.
Heal your knee. That's an order.

219
00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:58.639
[breathes deeply]

220
00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:00.891
[John] And the Waves drop game two.

221
00:10:00.975 --> 00:10:02.560
This one was never close. folks.

222
00:10:02.643 --> 00:10:06.939
No Marcus Winfield.
who wasn't even in the arena.

223
00:10:07.023 --> 00:10:11.277
LA will head to Boston with
their star player nowhere to be found.

224
00:10:12.486 --> 00:10:14.572
-[Isla sighs]
-Hey. package for Isla.

225
00:10:15.323 --> 00:10:18.117
These disguises are becoming less cute
the more games I lose.

226
00:10:18.701 --> 00:10:19.660
Is it still working?

227
00:10:21.495 --> 00:10:22.455
Yeah.

228
00:10:22.538 --> 00:10:24.165
[upbeat music playing]

229
00:10:24.248 --> 00:10:25.124
Yeah.

230
00:10:28.544 --> 00:10:29.712
[knocking]

231
00:10:29.795 --> 00:10:31.589
Aruna. my diva.

232
00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:34.759
How are you. mama?

233
00:10:34.842 --> 00:10:36.719
You didn't go with the team to Boston?

234
00:10:36.802 --> 00:10:38.346
And be away from my bestie?

235
00:10:40.181 --> 00:10:42.308
-Charcuterie?
-I can't. I'm pregnant.

236
00:10:42.391 --> 00:10:43.976
Literal mama!

237
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:50.483
Um. so I just wanted to close the loop
on the whole Cam rehab check situation

238
00:10:50.566 --> 00:10:53.903
and see how you decided to explain it.

239
00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:55.279
I did not decide anything.

240
00:10:55.363 --> 00:10:58.699
It was improperly filed.
so I brought it to your attention.

241
00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:03.954
Right. Right. Yeah.
but since we paid it back and Cam's gone.

242
00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:07.792
I'm assuming we can keep this between us?

243
00:11:07.875 --> 00:11:09.877
I see what you're trying to do here.

244
00:11:10.836 --> 00:11:12.713
-And I will keep your secret.
-Oh my God.

245
00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:14.840
Thank you. Aruna.

246
00:11:14.924 --> 00:11:17.051
Unless someone asks me. Then I cannot lie.

247
00:11:17.134 --> 00:11:18.302
What?

248
00:11:18.386 --> 00:11:19.887
No. Why?

249
00:11:19.970 --> 00:11:21.597
I don't have your family's loose morals.

250
00:11:22.181 --> 00:11:23.974
No. neither do I. I'm the good one.

251
00:11:24.058 --> 00:11:26.018
Whatever you have to tell yourself.

252
00:11:27.311 --> 00:11:28.562
-[exhales]
-[door closes]

253
00:11:32.191 --> 00:11:33.234
[whispering] Oh God.

254
00:11:33.317 --> 00:11:36.696
[John] And LA loses game three
of the finals in Boston.

255
00:11:36.779 --> 00:11:38.656
[analyst] And where's Marcus Winfield?

256
00:11:38.739 --> 00:11:39.740
It's over. Ali.

257
00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:41.033
No. it is not over.

258
00:11:41.117 --> 00:11:44.578
Yes. we are down three games to none.
Yes. no one's ever come back from that.

259
00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:47.665
But your blowout's still holding up.

260
00:11:49.875 --> 00:11:51.377
[screams]

261
00:11:51.460 --> 00:11:53.337
-What the…?
-Jay?!

262
00:11:53.421 --> 00:11:55.172
Oh. hey. this is nuts.

263
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:57.466
I. uh. thought this was my room.

264
00:11:57.550 --> 00:11:59.802
What are you talking about?
You live in this city.

265
00:11:59.885 --> 00:12:02.179
-I know. I know. It's so weird. I…
-[Ali] Oh. Oh.

266
00:12:02.263 --> 00:12:04.432
-Oh my God.
-Man. I am so mixed up.

267
00:12:04.515 --> 00:12:05.933
[Ali] Oh my God.

268
00:12:06.016 --> 00:12:07.268
I'm so sorry about that. Bye.

269
00:12:07.351 --> 00:12:09.353
[funky pop music playing]

270
00:12:11.731 --> 00:12:13.357
It started after we played the McShays.

271
00:12:13.441 --> 00:12:14.525
-[gasps]
-Ow!

272
00:12:14.608 --> 00:12:16.736
Stop not telling me
when you hook up with Jay!

273
00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:17.778
We kept texting.

274
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.781
and then when we made the finals.
it just became. like. a thing.

275
00:12:20.865 --> 00:12:23.159
Wow. So… so you're. like. dating?

276
00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:25.119
We're keeping it casual.
Living in the moment.

277
00:12:25.202 --> 00:12:26.203
[Ali scoffs]

278
00:12:26.287 --> 00:12:29.290
What? Ali.
long-distance relationships can work.

279
00:12:29.373 --> 00:12:30.666
I'm not trying to be harsh.

280
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.418
I know you're just living in the moment.

281
00:12:32.501 --> 00:12:35.087
but this moment is also
your chance to win a title.

282
00:12:36.505 --> 00:12:38.215
It's not the best timing. I'll admit it.

283
00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:40.634
Also. kinda risky
sleeping with the enemy during wartime.

284
00:12:40.718 --> 00:12:44.180
I'm not giving him our game plan
when we're. you know…

285
00:12:44.263 --> 00:12:46.223
Not that it'd matter.
Jay doesn't need help.

286
00:12:46.307 --> 00:12:48.225
Boston's dominated
every team in the playoffs.

287
00:12:48.309 --> 00:12:49.769
Not everyone. Not Chicago.

288
00:12:49.852 --> 00:12:50.686
True.

289
00:12:52.396 --> 00:12:54.607
[pensive music playing]

290
00:12:54.690 --> 00:12:56.734
-What?
-Get Ness in here right now.

291
00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:04.074
Boston won every series
by an average of nine points a game.

292
00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:05.075
except Chicago.

293
00:13:05.159 --> 00:13:07.077
That series.
they only won by three a game.

294
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:08.871
And two of those games went to overtime.

295
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:11.248
So what did Chicago do differently?

296
00:13:11.999 --> 00:13:15.377
They went small.
Four guards and a power forward.

297
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.047
Zone. nonstop press.
Totally changed up their game.

298
00:13:18.964 --> 00:13:20.466
We're gonna go Chicago-style.

299
00:13:20.549 --> 00:13:23.052
Attack from the wings.
put Turner and Kuman in foul trouble.

300
00:13:23.135 --> 00:13:24.804
take away their biggest advantage.

301
00:13:25.304 --> 00:13:26.388
Ness. what do we think?

302
00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:27.932
Chicago-style.

303
00:13:29.350 --> 00:13:30.476
I like it.

304
00:13:31.477 --> 00:13:35.314
It's also making me really want
some pizza. I'll get into it with Coach.

305
00:13:35.397 --> 00:13:36.357
[exhales]

306
00:13:37.525 --> 00:13:39.276
I wish you'd thought of this
three games ago.

307
00:13:40.236 --> 00:13:42.238
[gentle music playing]

308
00:13:44.448 --> 00:13:45.866
[knocking on door]

309
00:13:48.035 --> 00:13:48.869
Hey.

310
00:13:48.953 --> 00:13:50.204
Can we talk?

311
00:13:51.205 --> 00:13:55.709
I'm wondering if this is getting
a little… too complicated.

312
00:13:55.793 --> 00:13:58.212
and maybe we should push pause for a bit.

313
00:13:58.295 --> 00:14:00.589
-Is this because Ali saw me naked?
-No. no. no.

314
00:14:00.673 --> 00:14:04.051
I just…
I'm having a hard time focusing. I think.

315
00:14:05.511 --> 00:14:06.887
Focusing or losing?

316
00:14:07.388 --> 00:14:10.349
Come on. Don't tell me you wouldn't feel
similarly if you were down 0-3.

317
00:14:10.432 --> 00:14:14.144
Yeah. but I thought we talked about
keeping this and basketball separate.

318
00:14:14.228 --> 00:14:18.274
Yeah. well. we also didn't have pants on
when we made that decision. so…

319
00:14:18.357 --> 00:14:21.569
Can't we just figure this out
when the finals are over?

320
00:14:22.736 --> 00:14:23.571
Sure.

321
00:14:24.488 --> 00:14:25.322
Yeah.

322
00:14:26.740 --> 00:14:28.200
I can wait one more game.

323
00:14:30.953 --> 00:14:32.246
Are you talking shit?

324
00:14:32.746 --> 00:14:34.790
I mean. we're rivals again. so…

325
00:14:36.917 --> 00:14:37.751
Okay.

326
00:14:38.335 --> 00:14:39.336
Okay.

327
00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:40.337
Good luck.

328
00:14:40.421 --> 00:14:41.338
Good luck.

329
00:14:43.799 --> 00:14:45.801
[dramatic music playing]

330
00:14:49.847 --> 00:14:51.473
[buzzer blares]

331
00:14:52.057 --> 00:14:55.227
[John] And a shorthanded LA team
staves off elimination.

332
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:58.147
but Boston's still up three games to one.

333
00:14:58.230 --> 00:15:00.983
I mean. come on.
Chicago-style totally worked.

334
00:15:01.066 --> 00:15:02.860
Ooh. Jay was flustered the whole game.

335
00:15:02.943 --> 00:15:05.446
Did you see when he was choking
on Gatorade and started coughing?

336
00:15:05.529 --> 00:15:08.616
It was nice to see
his hot face sweaty and bloated.

337
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:09.909
just like the rest of us.

338
00:15:09.992 --> 00:15:11.493
Any update on Marcus?

339
00:15:11.577 --> 00:15:13.454
No. Ray and Roy both have
their phones off.

340
00:15:13.537 --> 00:15:17.041
I know he's pissed. but he should be
sitting on the bench supporting the guys.

341
00:15:17.124 --> 00:15:18.959
It's fine. all right?
We're gonna find him.

342
00:15:19.043 --> 00:15:20.002
-Cheer up.
-[groans]

343
00:15:20.085 --> 00:15:21.503
-You okay?
-Oh. sorry. Too hard?

344
00:15:21.587 --> 00:15:22.796
[all gasp]

345
00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:23.923
Is that your tooth?

346
00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:26.759
It's from all the gum you've been chewing.
Bitch. you just lost a tooth.

347
00:15:26.842 --> 00:15:29.178
We're gonna take you to the dentist
as soon as we get to LA.

348
00:15:29.261 --> 00:15:31.138
Jackie. go around! Drive! Jesus!

349
00:15:31.221 --> 00:15:34.475
We should look into separate flights home.
That could be contagious.

350
00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:38.812
Okay. Gene. just stay there for the month.

351
00:15:39.897 --> 00:15:42.483
Oh my God. I wasn't serious.

352
00:15:42.566 --> 00:15:43.901
-[exhales]
-[knock on door]

353
00:15:43.984 --> 00:15:45.945
Hey. everything okay?

354
00:15:46.445 --> 00:15:50.532
No. my husband wants to move
to Austin for his "stand-up" career.

355
00:15:50.616 --> 00:15:53.243
He thinks he's got a shot
at being Theo Von's assistant.

356
00:15:53.327 --> 00:15:54.244
[softly] Oh.

357
00:15:54.328 --> 00:15:55.496
Anyway. what's up?

358
00:15:56.538 --> 00:15:58.624
I think you should come
on the scouting trip.

359
00:15:58.707 --> 00:16:00.626
-What?
-You know the game.

360
00:16:00.709 --> 00:16:03.963
You're good at pointing out people's flaws
that make 'em human and weak.

361
00:16:04.046 --> 00:16:06.090
-I… I don't know. Ness.
-I could use the help.

362
00:16:06.173 --> 00:16:07.967
I mean. these kids see me
as the fun uncle.

363
00:16:08.050 --> 00:16:08.884
[scoffs]

364
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:10.886
It'd be good to know
they have a bitchy tiger mom.

365
00:16:10.970 --> 00:16:12.471
You could've just said tiger mom.

366
00:16:12.554 --> 00:16:13.973
Tiger mom.

367
00:16:14.056 --> 00:16:15.099
You know what?

368
00:16:17.351 --> 00:16:18.352
I'm in.

369
00:16:18.852 --> 00:16:19.979
All right.

370
00:16:20.479 --> 00:16:23.107
Just so you know. last time
I went transatlantic. I took an Ambien.

371
00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.859
and I just kinda wandered the aisles.
but I sorted that out.

372
00:16:25.943 --> 00:16:26.902
Monica!

373
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.570
[R&B music playing]

374
00:16:30.864 --> 00:16:31.699
[Isla] Oh.

375
00:16:32.241 --> 00:16:34.952
Isla. you must start flossing.

376
00:16:35.035 --> 00:16:37.413
I do.

377
00:16:37.496 --> 00:16:40.666
I just removed
an entire Cobb salad out of your mouth.

378
00:16:40.749 --> 00:16:41.875
Oh. Mr. McShay!

379
00:16:41.959 --> 00:16:44.670
-Hi.
-It's so good to see your gums. as usual.

380
00:16:44.753 --> 00:16:47.548
And I don't know how.
but your teeth are getting straighter.

381
00:16:47.631 --> 00:16:48.549
Good genes. I guess.

382
00:16:48.632 --> 00:16:49.550
[laughs]

383
00:16:51.593 --> 00:16:52.428
Hey.

384
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:54.596
What are you doing here?
Getting new teeth for your hockey players?

385
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:56.640
I've been coming to Dr. Weaver for years.

386
00:16:56.724 --> 00:16:57.599
Me too.

387
00:16:57.683 --> 00:17:01.186
He did my braces
when I was a kid and an adult.

388
00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:02.479
I mean. it's not a great flex.

389
00:17:02.563 --> 00:17:03.522
[both laugh]

390
00:17:03.605 --> 00:17:04.440
No.

391
00:17:05.024 --> 00:17:08.027
No. I'm a little off.
I haven't had solid foods all day.

392
00:17:08.110 --> 00:17:12.322
Well. lucky for you. this building has one
of the best restaurants in Los Angeles.

393
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:13.323
[slurps] Mmm.

394
00:17:13.407 --> 00:17:14.408
-Feeling better?
-Mm-hmm.

395
00:17:14.491 --> 00:17:17.286
-Blood sugar back to normal?
-Didn't this used to be a cigar lounge?

396
00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:20.581
And then a cupcake store
and a fedora shop.

397
00:17:20.664 --> 00:17:21.790
[Isla] Mmm.

398
00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:23.959
So you're riding high
after that W last night?

399
00:17:24.043 --> 00:17:25.961
Yeah. Oh.

400
00:17:26.045 --> 00:17:26.879
We needed that.

401
00:17:26.962 --> 00:17:29.631
It was a good call changing up
the game plan. They weren't ready.

402
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:30.632
You watched.

403
00:17:30.716 --> 00:17:33.635
Are you kidding? I'm from LA.
I love everything about this city.

404
00:17:33.719 --> 00:17:36.055
I mean. except the 405.

405
00:17:36.555 --> 00:17:37.389
The worst.

406
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:39.850
-Oh. what about the 110? Horrible.
-Horrible.

407
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:42.061
I love exiting from the left side
like an idiot.

408
00:17:43.687 --> 00:17:46.815
You see? I knew we'd have a good time
if we went out on a date.

409
00:17:46.899 --> 00:17:48.609
-This is not a date.
-It's not a date?

410
00:17:48.692 --> 00:17:51.320
No. it's two people talking
in a medical plaza.

411
00:17:51.904 --> 00:17:52.738
All right.

412
00:17:52.821 --> 00:17:55.824
-Well. let's do dinner next time.
-Not so fast.

413
00:17:55.908 --> 00:17:58.786
Maybe we'll run into each other
at the podiatrist.

414
00:17:58.869 --> 00:18:00.704
[hip-hop music playing]

415
00:18:01.330 --> 00:18:03.665
[John] Dyson for three. Good again!

416
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:06.335
And the Waves have come from behind
to win game five.

417
00:18:06.418 --> 00:18:09.213
Game six has been all Waves.

418
00:18:09.296 --> 00:18:10.672
Travis to Tommy.

419
00:18:10.756 --> 00:18:14.635
And the Waves win big in Boston
to force game seven.

420
00:18:14.718 --> 00:18:16.386
[analyst] Insane win. John.

421
00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:19.473
[John] Can Isla Gordon bring home
her first title as Team Pres?

422
00:18:19.556 --> 00:18:20.974
We'll find out tonight.

423
00:18:22.684 --> 00:18:23.936
Jackie!

424
00:18:25.354 --> 00:18:27.523
Hey. any word if Marcus showed up yet?

425
00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.483
-Nothing.
-Oh. shit.

426
00:18:29.566 --> 00:18:31.735
I took away all your gum.
Dr. Weaver's orders.

427
00:18:31.819 --> 00:18:34.363
If you want something to chew on.
I have soft cheeses and oatmeal

428
00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:35.280
in the break room.

429
00:18:35.364 --> 00:18:36.365
[exhales]

430
00:18:37.157 --> 00:18:38.117
Thanks.

431
00:18:40.077 --> 00:18:41.870
Jackie. sit down for a second.

432
00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:48.627
Look. Cam was wrong about a lot.
but he wasn't about one thing.

433
00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:50.003
That taxation is theft?

434
00:18:50.087 --> 00:18:50.921
No.

435
00:18:51.004 --> 00:18:53.006
You deserve more opportunity here.

436
00:18:53.715 --> 00:18:56.218
How'd you like to go with Ness
on the scouting trip to Europe?

437
00:18:56.301 --> 00:18:58.178
[chuckling] Are you serious?

438
00:18:58.262 --> 00:19:00.889
-Yes.
-I've been dying to visit Europe.

439
00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:02.933
Ooh. it's my favorite part
of It's a Small World.

440
00:19:03.016 --> 00:19:04.101
Great.

441
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:07.771
But I think I have to pass.

442
00:19:09.189 --> 00:19:10.816
Really? Why?

443
00:19:10.899 --> 00:19:12.776
I've been meaning
to talk to you about this.

444
00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:15.445
You know Sofia's doing
her internship in DC.

445
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:18.991
and I was kinda hoping
that I could take some time off

446
00:19:19.074 --> 00:19:20.367
to visit her for the summer.

447
00:19:20.450 --> 00:19:22.244
Oh. that's nice.

448
00:19:22.327 --> 00:19:23.328
Um…

449
00:19:24.037 --> 00:19:25.914
But what are you going to do
while you're there?

450
00:19:25.998 --> 00:19:30.252
Um. help her get ready
for work in the mornings. and then.

451
00:19:31.378 --> 00:19:33.172
I don't know. wait until she gets home.

452
00:19:33.755 --> 00:19:34.631
Jackie…

453
00:19:36.508 --> 00:19:38.260
I have this friend.

454
00:19:38.343 --> 00:19:44.183
and… she got offered
a dream job in Paris. and turned it down

455
00:19:44.266 --> 00:19:48.812
because she wanted
to spend the summer with her boyfriend.

456
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:52.691
And then. a month later. they broke up.

457
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:57.738
And she will always be known
as the girl who didn't go to Paris.

458
00:19:57.821 --> 00:19:58.822
Wow.

459
00:19:59.406 --> 00:20:01.783
That sounds just like LC from The Hills.

460
00:20:01.867 --> 00:20:05.245
It is LC from The Hills.
She's my friend. I love her.

461
00:20:05.329 --> 00:20:08.957
But… do you want to be like LC?

462
00:20:11.001 --> 00:20:13.295
[rock music playing]

463
00:20:14.171 --> 00:20:16.965
[John] Welcome to game seven
of the ABL Finals.

464
00:20:17.049 --> 00:20:20.719
LA versus Boston. Winner take all.

465
00:20:21.220 --> 00:20:22.971
-You ready? Nervous?
-Hmm.

466
00:20:23.805 --> 00:20:25.515
-A little bit of both.
-[chuckles]

467
00:20:25.599 --> 00:20:27.267
[breathes deeply]

468
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:30.062
All right. let's go have
the best or worst night of my life.

469
00:20:30.145 --> 00:20:33.065
["This is the Moment"
by Koda Kids & Leslie Powell playing]

470
00:20:35.400 --> 00:20:36.902
♪ This is it ♪

471
00:20:36.985 --> 00:20:39.613
♪ Oh. oh. oh ♪

472
00:20:39.696 --> 00:20:40.906
♪ You got the power ♪

473
00:20:40.989 --> 00:20:43.283
♪ Oh. oh. oh ♪

474
00:20:43.367 --> 00:20:45.035
♪ This is the future… ♪

475
00:20:45.619 --> 00:20:46.703
-It'll be fun.
-Good luck.

476
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:47.621
You too.

477
00:20:47.704 --> 00:20:48.997
♪ This is the moment… ♪

478
00:20:49.665 --> 00:20:51.959
[announcer] Sign up for
an official Waves credit card

479
00:20:52.042 --> 00:20:53.627
and receive a free miniature…

480
00:20:53.710 --> 00:20:56.129
[buzzer blares]

481
00:20:56.213 --> 00:20:58.006
I can't believe Marcus is still MIA.

482
00:20:58.090 --> 00:21:01.134
[Isla] God. he can hate me all he wants.
but it's insane he's not here.

483
00:21:01.218 --> 00:21:03.553
[announcer] Make some noise!

484
00:21:03.637 --> 00:21:05.389
[John] All right. we're about ready to go.

485
00:21:05.472 --> 00:21:07.391
Game seven. You ready. Edgar?

486
00:21:07.474 --> 00:21:09.977
[Edgar] I'm ready
to run through a brick wall. John.

487
00:21:10.060 --> 00:21:11.812
[John] Maybe after the game.

488
00:21:11.895 --> 00:21:12.980
And we're off.

489
00:21:13.063 --> 00:21:16.984
Boston controls it.
and Howard leaps for the quick dunk.

490
00:21:17.567 --> 00:21:19.194
Waves' ball.

491
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.321
White calls out the play.

492
00:21:22.781 --> 00:21:24.741
Dyson off the curl.

493
00:21:24.825 --> 00:21:25.909
Not close.

494
00:21:26.410 --> 00:21:30.038
[Edgar] He's off early.
and Howard with another easy one.

495
00:21:30.122 --> 00:21:31.373
Put a body on him.

496
00:21:31.456 --> 00:21:32.416
[Edgar] He's killing us.

497
00:21:32.499 --> 00:21:35.419
[John] And a much bigger Boston team
is coming out hot.

498
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:36.670
[Norm] Come on. Come on.

499
00:21:37.713 --> 00:21:40.173
-[John] Tommy is stripped.
-Get back. Get back.

500
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:42.801
[Edgar] LA's down 20.

501
00:21:42.884 --> 00:21:45.846
[John] Jay Brown and Boston have figured
out how to handle LA's new scheme

502
00:21:45.929 --> 00:21:48.015
with a counterattack of their own.

503
00:21:48.098 --> 00:21:49.349
[indistinct chatter]

504
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:51.351
[club music playing faintly]

505
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:55.689
-Mmm. Sorry.
-Thank you. Thank you.

506
00:21:56.189 --> 00:21:57.190
Is that a mai tai?

507
00:21:57.274 --> 00:21:59.026
-This is an AMF.
-AMF?

508
00:21:59.109 --> 00:22:00.027
Goodbye. motherfucker.

509
00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:01.945
-Jackie.
-That's what the drink's called.

510
00:22:02.029 --> 00:22:04.072
[in Spanish] Yes. brother.

511
00:22:04.156 --> 00:22:06.950
I'm thinking
we should go to Dubrovnik for a day.

512
00:22:07.034 --> 00:22:09.911
Because they got this kid
that can drain threes from half court.

513
00:22:09.995 --> 00:22:12.080
Plus. shrimp capital of Eastern Europe.

514
00:22:12.164 --> 00:22:13.915
Look. if it's got a beach. I'm in.

515
00:22:13.999 --> 00:22:16.335
What. are you guys planning
a work trip or your honeymoon?

516
00:22:16.418 --> 00:22:17.419
-[Sandy chuckles]
-What?

517
00:22:17.502 --> 00:22:18.920
What are you talking about. Sandy?

518
00:22:19.004 --> 00:22:22.591
I get the Cam situation is making
you anxious. but you're a sloppy drunk.

519
00:22:22.674 --> 00:22:25.218
You need a cup of coffee.
Gail. can we get a coffee?

520
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:26.261
[Ali] Yeah. we're done.

521
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:28.430
Coffee and an AMF. Gail.

522
00:22:28.513 --> 00:22:29.473
Shh. shh. shh. shh.

523
00:22:29.556 --> 00:22:31.266
[John] We're almost ready
for the second half.

524
00:22:31.350 --> 00:22:34.603
but the Waves without Marcus Winfield
are down big.

525
00:22:34.686 --> 00:22:35.812
[Ali] Jay is pretty focused.

526
00:22:37.939 --> 00:22:38.982
All right. guys.

527
00:22:39.483 --> 00:22:42.110
I know it may seem impossible right now.

528
00:22:42.194 --> 00:22:45.280
and it might be impossible.
but that doesn't mean it's not possible.

529
00:22:45.364 --> 00:22:47.115
Coach. that's literally what it means.

530
00:22:47.199 --> 00:22:48.075
[growls]

531
00:22:48.158 --> 00:22:50.160
-[crowd cheering]
-[cameras clicking]

532
00:22:51.536 --> 00:22:54.581
[announcer] Now entering
the arena. Marcus Winfield!

533
00:22:54.664 --> 00:22:56.917
-[Travis] Where the hell you been?
-China. baby.

534
00:22:57.000 --> 00:22:58.668
-[laughs]
-Just got back an hour ago.

535
00:22:58.752 --> 00:22:59.920
Whoa. whoa. What?

536
00:23:00.003 --> 00:23:01.296
There's a lab in Chengdu.

537
00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:03.799
They have experimental therapy
that isn't available anywhere else.

538
00:23:03.882 --> 00:23:05.634
-Can you play?
-I'm playing.

539
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:07.511
-[Benson] Yeah!
-All right. All right.

540
00:23:08.011 --> 00:23:09.763
Hey. listen. guys. One more thing.

541
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:15.268
I want to tell you all
about the night that I met my late wife.

542
00:23:15.352 --> 00:23:17.229
It was October 1990.

543
00:23:17.312 --> 00:23:22.901
And I know that because it was
the original Aunt Viv from Fresh Prince.

544
00:23:23.443 --> 00:23:25.862
It might have been '91.
and I was watching Roseanne.

545
00:23:25.946 --> 00:23:28.448
-The point is--
-All right. Coach. Do you mind?

546
00:23:29.324 --> 00:23:31.034
-[exhales]
-Let me help you out.

547
00:23:31.118 --> 00:23:32.911
[exhales] Yeah. thank you.

548
00:23:32.994 --> 00:23:36.164
Look. we all know
you miss your dead wife. all right?

549
00:23:36.248 --> 00:23:38.959
But if she's watching right now.
she wants one thing.

550
00:23:39.459 --> 00:23:41.545
To win this fucking game!

551
00:23:41.628 --> 00:23:42.629
[all scream]

552
00:23:43.255 --> 00:23:44.506
Waves on three!

553
00:23:44.589 --> 00:23:46.591
-[Marcus] One. two. three. Waves!
-[players] Waves!

554
00:23:47.092 --> 00:23:48.135
[Norm] It was Golden Girls.

555
00:23:48.218 --> 00:23:49.261
[John] I don't believe it.

556
00:23:49.344 --> 00:23:53.056
Look at this. Marcus Winfield is starting
the second half.

557
00:23:53.849 --> 00:23:55.100
Where have you been?

558
00:23:55.183 --> 00:23:58.061
You told me to get better.
so… I got better.

559
00:23:58.645 --> 00:23:59.980
[buzzer blares]

560
00:24:01.231 --> 00:24:04.109
[John] And we're underway
in the second half.

561
00:24:04.192 --> 00:24:07.988
Marcus Winfield is back.
and he's picking up full court.

562
00:24:08.780 --> 00:24:11.908
He pokes it away from Turner.
Winfield on a breakaway.

563
00:24:11.992 --> 00:24:14.244
-[whistle blows]
-[John] Bucket and a foul!

564
00:24:14.327 --> 00:24:16.163
-And one!
-What? Who?

565
00:24:16.246 --> 00:24:17.789
That's Turner's fourth. Very good!

566
00:24:17.873 --> 00:24:19.499
[John] Waves on the attack again.

567
00:24:19.583 --> 00:24:20.667
Tommy White penetrates.

568
00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:22.461
Don't give him that! Don't give him that!

569
00:24:22.544 --> 00:24:23.670
[John] To Marcus.

570
00:24:24.713 --> 00:24:26.131
It's good!

571
00:24:26.882 --> 00:24:28.216
Pressure. guys. Pressure!

572
00:24:29.342 --> 00:24:30.343
[crowd chanting] Defense!

573
00:24:30.427 --> 00:24:33.096
[John] LA continues
the defensive pressure. Turner has it.

574
00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:34.473
He… misses.

575
00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:36.600
Up ahead to Gibbs.

576
00:24:36.683 --> 00:24:39.060
He finds Tommy for three.

577
00:24:39.811 --> 00:24:41.354
-It's good!
-[crowd cheering]

578
00:24:42.272 --> 00:24:44.274
We need a stop. We need a stop.

579
00:24:45.025 --> 00:24:47.611
[John] LA's defense has
turned it up a notch.

580
00:24:47.694 --> 00:24:48.778
Another steal.

581
00:24:49.362 --> 00:24:51.698
Atkins leaves it for Edwards.

582
00:24:51.781 --> 00:24:54.451
-Slam dunk!
-[crowd cheering]

583
00:24:54.534 --> 00:24:56.453
He's panicking. Jay's panicking.

584
00:24:58.914 --> 00:25:00.540
[Edgar] Less than a minute to go. John.

585
00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:03.376
The Waves gotta get something
on this possession.

586
00:25:03.460 --> 00:25:04.794
[whistle blows]

587
00:25:04.878 --> 00:25:05.879
[John] Foul!

588
00:25:05.962 --> 00:25:09.633
Adrian Turner.
Boston's leading scorer. has fouled out.

589
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:12.636
[John] And LA has fought back.
Thirty seconds left.

590
00:25:12.719 --> 00:25:14.513
And now trails by four.

591
00:25:14.596 --> 00:25:15.680
Let's go!

592
00:25:17.349 --> 00:25:18.183
Don't let up.

593
00:25:18.266 --> 00:25:19.643
[John] LA applying the pressure.

594
00:25:19.726 --> 00:25:21.686
Boston needs to get a shot off.

595
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:23.647
-No good!
-Get back! Get back!

596
00:25:23.730 --> 00:25:26.483
[John] LA needs a quick one here.
Ball goes to Victor in the corner.

597
00:25:26.566 --> 00:25:27.943
He swings it to Dyson.

598
00:25:28.026 --> 00:25:29.986
Gibbs for three!

599
00:25:30.070 --> 00:25:31.780
-It's good!
-[crowd cheers]

600
00:25:31.863 --> 00:25:33.240
Waves down by one.

601
00:25:33.323 --> 00:25:36.201
Boston ball. Ten seconds left.

602
00:25:36.284 --> 00:25:37.285
[Edgar] LA's gotta foul!

603
00:25:37.369 --> 00:25:40.747
-[John] Here's the game. Stolen by Marcus!
-Time-out!

604
00:25:40.830 --> 00:25:42.207
Time-out. Waves!

605
00:25:42.707 --> 00:25:45.085
[Edgar] He's playing like a man possessed.

606
00:25:45.168 --> 00:25:47.379
-[Ness] Whoa!
-[Sandy] Whoo!

607
00:25:47.462 --> 00:25:49.214
-Yes!
-Oh my God.

608
00:25:49.297 --> 00:25:52.008
I'm gonna throw up.
Ali. did you bring a vomit bag?

609
00:25:52.092 --> 00:25:53.301
Yes. but Ness already used it.

610
00:25:53.385 --> 00:25:55.929
Are you guys nervous.
or do you have norovirus?

611
00:25:56.012 --> 00:25:57.764
-Jesus.
-[Ness] 'Cause of all the stress.

612
00:25:58.265 --> 00:25:59.599
[John] What a game.

613
00:25:59.683 --> 00:26:02.143
It all comes down to this.

614
00:26:02.227 --> 00:26:03.895
-[whistle blows]
-[John] Game on the line.

615
00:26:03.979 --> 00:26:05.146
Title on the line.

616
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:07.065
Waves have the ball.

617
00:26:07.148 --> 00:26:08.316
They bring it in to Tommy

618
00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:10.860
who gets it to Winfield
at the top of the key.

619
00:26:10.944 --> 00:26:15.323
[Edgar] Boston can't double Marcus
because LA's shooters have been red-hot.

620
00:26:15.865 --> 00:26:19.035
[John] He drives. pulls it back…

621
00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:22.497
elevates.

622
00:26:23.498 --> 00:26:24.874
For the win…

623
00:26:26.167 --> 00:26:27.919
[Ali mouthing]

624
00:26:28.003 --> 00:26:30.171
You need to trade for
a shooting guard who can hit a three.

625
00:26:30.255 --> 00:26:31.715
You're gonna come work for us.

626
00:26:31.798 --> 00:26:33.133
-[whistle blows]
-[cheering]

627
00:26:33.216 --> 00:26:35.635
I'm making you the president of the Waves.

628
00:26:35.719 --> 00:26:37.429
Done. Sending you a deal memo.

629
00:26:37.512 --> 00:26:39.639
[uplifting music playing]

630
00:26:39.723 --> 00:26:43.018
There will always be
another playoffs that you choose over me.

631
00:26:43.101 --> 00:26:45.604
[music continues]

632
00:26:50.191 --> 00:26:51.067
[buzzer blares]

633
00:26:51.151 --> 00:26:52.068
[ball swooshes]

634
00:26:52.736 --> 00:26:55.196
[John] It's good! It's good! It's good!

635
00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:56.489
Waves win!

636
00:26:57.073 --> 00:26:58.908
Marcus Winfield is the hero!

637
00:26:59.451 --> 00:27:02.787
The Waves are the world champions!

638
00:27:02.871 --> 00:27:04.664
[crowd cheering]

639
00:27:04.748 --> 00:27:06.750
[uplifting music playing]

640
00:27:23.141 --> 00:27:25.644
[hip-hop music playing]

641
00:27:25.727 --> 00:27:27.937
[inaudible]

642
00:27:29.439 --> 00:27:31.983
-Norm! You did it!
-All right. Hey.

643
00:27:32.067 --> 00:27:32.901
[both laugh]

644
00:27:32.984 --> 00:27:33.818
[Norm] Yeah.

645
00:27:34.402 --> 00:27:38.823
Thank you. Thank you so much
for just believing in me. you know?

646
00:27:38.907 --> 00:27:40.700
I mean. when Andrea passed.

647
00:27:40.784 --> 00:27:45.121
I thought I would just be that old guy
who goes to the racetrack every day

648
00:27:45.205 --> 00:27:49.376
until the janitor comes
and sees me dead in the toilet stall.

649
00:27:49.459 --> 00:27:52.045
But you gave me
the dignity that I so badly needed.

650
00:27:52.128 --> 00:27:54.673
Norm. Norm. I… I love you. I love you.

651
00:27:54.756 --> 00:27:56.841
It's too… too heavy a conversation
for this time.

652
00:27:56.925 --> 00:27:58.093
-Okay.
-Congrats. Norm.

653
00:27:58.176 --> 00:27:59.010
You too.

654
00:27:59.094 --> 00:28:00.220
[both laugh]

655
00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:02.138
All right.

656
00:28:02.222 --> 00:28:03.139
-Hmm.
-We're good.

657
00:28:04.974 --> 00:28:08.937
-Yeah. I mean. I guess the best part--
-Champagne! That's the best part!

658
00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:10.730
Jackie. come here!

659
00:28:11.231 --> 00:28:12.941
-Congrats. sis.
-[sighs]

660
00:28:13.024 --> 00:28:15.443
So I told Sofia
I'm going to Europe this summer.

661
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.320
Oh. that's amazing!

662
00:28:17.404 --> 00:28:18.697
How'd she take it?

663
00:28:19.197 --> 00:28:20.907
-Not well.
-Oh.

664
00:28:20.990 --> 00:28:23.535
But I didn't wanna be
the girl who didn't go to Paris.

665
00:28:24.035 --> 00:28:26.037
Oh. Ooh.

666
00:28:26.121 --> 00:28:27.414
Oh yeah!

667
00:28:29.249 --> 00:28:32.043
Brielle. will you make me
the luckiest man in the world?

668
00:28:32.127 --> 00:28:33.920
Will you have a threesome with me tonight?

669
00:28:34.003 --> 00:28:36.047
With that thot sitting courtside?

670
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:38.341
-Yeah.
-Baby. I thought you'd never ask!

671
00:28:41.052 --> 00:28:42.679
[chuckles] Oh. Marcus.

672
00:28:44.305 --> 00:28:45.849
-We did it.
-Yeah.

673
00:28:45.932 --> 00:28:48.059
-Oh.
-Good news is it's not my knee.

674
00:28:48.143 --> 00:28:51.354
Oh good. That is very. very good news.

675
00:28:51.438 --> 00:28:52.981
It's my Achilles.

676
00:28:55.900 --> 00:28:56.776
What?

677
00:28:57.902 --> 00:29:00.113
-We gotta get you to Dr. Haber right--
-Later.

678
00:29:01.322 --> 00:29:04.492
I don't wanna spend my last moments
as a player inside a training room.

679
00:29:04.576 --> 00:29:06.619
[hip-hop music playing indistinctly]

680
00:29:10.123 --> 00:29:10.957
[exhales]

681
00:29:11.624 --> 00:29:12.959
Smile. We won.

682
00:29:16.379 --> 00:29:17.964
Oh. thank you. Marcus.

683
00:29:19.674 --> 00:29:20.675
Thank you.

684
00:29:22.552 --> 00:29:23.595
Now help me up.

685
00:29:24.262 --> 00:29:25.096
Please.

686
00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:26.765
[players cheering]

687
00:29:26.848 --> 00:29:28.266
[hip-hop music playing]

688
00:29:28.349 --> 00:29:31.352
♪ There's not enough room
For the both of us. look ♪

689
00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:33.521
♪ If you ever callin' me
Call me number one ♪

690
00:29:33.605 --> 00:29:35.523
♪ Oops. I did it again ♪

691
00:29:35.607 --> 00:29:36.900
[music stops abruptly]

692
00:29:36.983 --> 00:29:38.151
[birds chirping]

693
00:29:38.234 --> 00:29:39.277
[inhales deeply]

694
00:29:41.696 --> 00:29:42.739
[moans]

695
00:29:43.364 --> 00:29:45.241
-[moans]
-[phone vibrating]

696
00:29:49.287 --> 00:29:50.205
[chuckles lightly]

697
00:29:53.041 --> 00:29:54.125
[chuckles]

698
00:29:57.587 --> 00:29:58.797
-[gasps]
-[body thuds]

699
00:29:59.672 --> 00:30:00.965
[Isla exhales deeply]

700
00:30:01.049 --> 00:30:03.051
[gentle music playing]

701
00:30:13.269 --> 00:30:14.312
[Isla exhales]

702
00:30:17.607 --> 00:30:18.650
[Ali groans]

703
00:30:19.692 --> 00:30:20.777
Oh.

704
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:22.237
God. he's so sweaty.

705
00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:25.949
If I would've known I'd be this hungover.
I maybe would've wanted to lose.

706
00:30:26.032 --> 00:30:29.536
No offense. but your voice sounds like
someone is drilling a hole in my brain.

707
00:30:29.619 --> 00:30:30.787
[groans]

708
00:30:31.663 --> 00:30:33.039
[Sandy] Oh God.

709
00:30:33.122 --> 00:30:33.998
[Ali. Isla chuckle]

710
00:30:34.582 --> 00:30:35.792
Oh. I feel horrible.

711
00:30:35.875 --> 00:30:37.544
[groans]

712
00:30:37.627 --> 00:30:38.628
What?

713
00:30:39.128 --> 00:30:40.964
-Oh no.
-What is that?

714
00:30:41.047 --> 00:30:42.549
You passed out grilling steaks.

715
00:30:42.632 --> 00:30:44.384
-Oh!
-You need to go to the hospital.

716
00:30:44.467 --> 00:30:45.844
Turn the TV on right now.

717
00:30:46.344 --> 00:30:47.178
Jackie.

718
00:30:47.262 --> 00:30:48.930
Oh. what the f…

719
00:30:49.013 --> 00:30:52.475
The LA Industry basketball franchise
was an integral part of this city.

720
00:30:52.559 --> 00:30:54.310
-What is this.
-[Al] Until it moved.

721
00:30:54.394 --> 00:30:57.522
But today. the Industry has returned.

722
00:30:57.605 --> 00:31:02.277
And we're gonna be the best
basketball team in Los Angeles! [laughs]

723
00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:03.528
Holy shit.

724
00:31:03.611 --> 00:31:04.529
What is happening?

725
00:31:04.612 --> 00:31:07.907
I am so honored
to partner with Al Fleischman

726
00:31:07.991 --> 00:31:09.742
to purchase the Industry.

727
00:31:09.826 --> 00:31:14.247
Uh. I've only known Al a short time.
but he's already become like family to me.

728
00:31:14.330 --> 00:31:15.582
Oh my God.

729
00:31:15.665 --> 00:31:18.167
Now. if you're gonna have
a top-level basketball team.

730
00:31:18.251 --> 00:31:20.545
you are gonna need a top-level coach.

731
00:31:20.628 --> 00:31:23.590
so we pulled out all the stops
when we were hiring this guy.

732
00:31:23.673 --> 00:31:26.384
Um. I am so honored to introduce

733
00:31:26.467 --> 00:31:30.013
our new head coach
for the LA Industry and part owner.

734
00:31:30.096 --> 00:31:30.930
Jay Brown.

735
00:31:31.014 --> 00:31:32.181
-[applause]
-[Cam laughing]

736
00:31:32.265 --> 00:31:33.141
Come here.

737
00:31:33.224 --> 00:31:34.851
[Cam laughs]

738
00:31:34.934 --> 00:31:37.478
[Cam] Thanks. guys.
Come on. take a picture.

739
00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:39.606
[laughs]

740
00:31:39.689 --> 00:31:41.357
Motherfucker!

741
00:31:41.441 --> 00:31:42.275
♪ Hey. hey. hey ♪

742
00:31:42.358 --> 00:31:44.193
♪ Everywhere I go
I’m the life of the party ♪

743
00:31:44.277 --> 00:31:45.486
♪ Yo. that’s all I know. huh ♪

744
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:47.488
♪ My light shine bright
Like the sun with a glow ♪

745
00:31:47.572 --> 00:31:50.700
♪ And I bring the good vibes
Everywhere that I go. yeah. huh ♪

746
00:31:50.783 --> 00:31:53.912
♪ Everywhere I be. I’m walking with a swag
Like you wouldn’t believe ♪

747
00:31:53.995 --> 00:31:56.080
♪ They be looking. they be jocking
They be rocking with me ♪

748
00:31:56.164 --> 00:31:58.166
♪ Everybody wanna be
Everywhere that I be ♪

749
00:31:58.249 --> 00:32:00.335
♪ It goes one. two. three. four. five ♪

750
